SIMPLE: manchineel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manchineel
<hw>Man`chi*neel"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>manzanillo</ets>, fr. <ets>manzana</ets> an apple, fr. L.
<ets>malum Matianum</ets> a kind of apple. So called from its apple-like
fruit.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A euphorbiaceous tree
(<spn>Hippomane Mancinella</spn>) of tropical America, having a
poisonous and blistering milky juice, and poisonous acrid fruit somewhat
resembling an apple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bastard manchineel</b></col>, <cd>a tree (<spn>Cameraria
latifolia</spn>) of the East Indies, having similar poisonous
properties.</cd> <au>Lindley.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manchu</ent>⟦br⟧
